FBIS4-4028 "drchi082_d_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-082 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 Northeast Asia Japan's Socialists Quit Ruling Coalition Japan's Socialists Quit Ruling Coalition OW2604001894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1710 GMT 25 Apr 94 OW2604001894 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Japan's socialists quit the ruling coalition on Tuesday [26 April], NHK Public Television said. The socialists' move is plunging Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata's government into crisis just hours after they helped to elect him. Hata is expected to form his new cabinet on Monday after winning a parliamentary vote earlier in the day.
